acdSfp.name: acdSfp

revisions.description: Add acdSfpInfoIdType, acdSfpInfoExtIdType and acdSfpInfoTransCode support.
Initial version of MIB module ACD-SFP-MIB.

acdSfp.description: The SFPs database for this Accedian Networks device.

acdSfpInfoEntry.name: acdSfpInfoEntry
acdSfpInfoEntry.description: This is a part of the content of the SFP's 0xA0 EEPROM

acdSfpInfoID.name: acdSfpInfoID
acdSfpInfoID.description: Unique value for each SFP. Its value ranges from 1 to MAXINT (4 bytes).

acdSfpInfoConnIdx.name: acdSfpInfoConnIdx
acdSfpInfoConnIdx.description: This object identifies the connector index on the box. The index is assigned form left to rigth starting with 1.

acdSfpInfoConnType.name: acdSfpInfoConnType
acdSfpInfoConnType.description: The connector value indicates the external optical or electrical cable connector provided as the media interface.

acdSfpInfoVendor.name: acdSfpInfoVendor
acdSfpInfoVendor.description: The vendor name is a 16 character field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces (20h). The vendor name shall be the full name of the corporation, a commonly accepted abbreviation of the name of the corporation, the SCSI company code for the corporation, or the stock exchange code for the corporation. At least one of the vendor name or the vendor OUI fields shall contain valid serial data.

acdSfpInfoVendorOui.name: acdSfpInfoVendorOui
acdSfpInfoVendorOui.description: The vendor organizationally unique identifier field (vendor OUI) is a 3-byte field that contains the IEEE Company Identifier for the vendor. A value of all zero in the 3-byte field indicates that the Vendor OUI is unspecified.

acdSfpInfoVendorPn.name: acdSfpInfoVendorPn
acdSfpInfoVendorPn.description: The vendor part number (vendor PN) is a 16-byte field that contains ASCII characters, leftaligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces (20h), defining the vendor's part number or product name. A value of all zero in the 16-byte field indicates that the vendor PN is unspecified.

acdSfpInfoVendorRev.name: acdSfpInfoVendorRev
acdSfpInfoVendorRev.description: The vendor revision number (vendor rev) is a 4-byte field that contains ASCII characters, leftaligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces (20h), defining the vendor's product revision number. A value of all zero in the 4-byte field indicates that the vendor PN is unspecified.

acdSfpInfoWavelength.name: acdSfpInfoWavelength
acdSfpInfoWavelength.description: Nominal transmitter output wavelength at room temperature. 16 bit value with byte 60 as high order byte and byte 61 as low order byte. The laser wavelength is equal to the 16 bit integer value in nm. This field allows the user to read the laser wavelength directly, so it is not necessary to infer it from the transceiver Code for Electronic Compatibility.

acdSfpInfoSerialNum.name: acdSfpInfoSerialNum
acdSfpInfoSerialNum.description: The vendor serial number (vendor SN) is a 16 character field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces (20h), defining the vendor's serial number for the transceiver. A value of all zero in the 16-byte field indicates that the vendor PN is unspecified.

acdSfpInfoYear.name: acdSfpInfoYear
acdSfpInfoYear.description: This is the year of manufacturing.

acdSfpInfoMonth.name: acdSfpInfoMonth
acdSfpInfoMonth.description: This is the month of manufacturing.

acdSfpInfoDay.name: acdSfpInfoDay
acdSfpInfoDay.description: This is the day of manufacturing.

acdSfpInfoLot.name: acdSfpInfoLot
acdSfpInfoLot.description: This is the Lot number of manufacturing.

acdSfpInfoRev8472.name: acdSfpInfoRev8472
acdSfpInfoRev8472.description: This is to indicate to which revision this SFP is compatible.

acdSfpInfoPresent.name: acdSfpInfoPresent
acdSfpInfoPresent.description: This is to indicate if the SFP is present or not.

acdSfpInfoDiag.name: acdSfpInfoDiag
acdSfpInfoDiag.description: This is to indicate if the SFP supports Digital Diagnostics.

acdSfpInfoInternal.name: acdSfpInfoInternal
acdSfpInfoInternal.description: This is to indicate if the SFP supports internal calibration. If externally calibrated, the measurements are raw A/D values and must be converted to real world units using calibration constants stored in EEPROM locations 56 to 95 at 2 wire serial bus address A2h. Calibration is valid over vendor specified operating temperature and voltage. Alarm and warning threshold values should be interpreted in the same manner as real time 16 bit data.

acdSfpInfoAlm.name: acdSfpInfoAlm
acdSfpInfoAlm.description: This is to indicate if the SFP supports Alarm and warning thresholds for the Digital Diagnostics.

acdSfpInfoIdType.name: acdSfpInfoIdType
acdSfpInfoIdType.description: The identifier value specifies the physical device described by the two-wire interface information. This value shall be included in the two-wire interface data (see SFF-8472 for details).

acdSfpInfoExtIdType.name: acdSfpInfoExtIdType
acdSfpInfoExtIdType.description: The extended identifier value provides additional information about the transceiver. The field should be set to 04h for all SFP modules indicating two-wire interface ID module definition (see SFF-8472 for details).

acdSfpInfoTransCode.name: acdSfpInfoTransCode
acdSfpInfoTransCode.description: The following bit significant indicators define the electronic or optical interfaces that are supported by the transceiver. At least one bit shall be set in this field (see SFF-8472 for details).

acdSfpDiagTable.name: acdSfpDiagTable
acdSfpDiagTable.description: Table of all SFP Digital Diagnostics

acdSfpDiagEntry.name: acdSfpDiagEntry
acdSfpDiagEntry.description: This is a part the content of the SFP's 0xA0 EEPROM

acdSfpDiagID.name: acdSfpDiagID
acdSfpDiagID.description: Unique value for each SFP. Its value ranges from 1 to MAXINT (4 bytes).

acdSfpDiagConnIdx.name: acdSfpDiagConnIdx

acdSfpDiagTemp.name: acdSfpDiagTemp
acdSfpDiagTemp.description: Internally measured transceiver temperature. Represented as a 16 bit signed twos complement value in degrees Celsius, yielding a total range of -128C to +128C.

acdSfpDiagVcc.name: acdSfpDiagVcc
acdSfpDiagVcc.description: Internally measured transceiver supply voltage. Represented as a 16 bit unsigned integer with the voltage defined as the full 16 bit value (0 to 65535) with LSB equal to 100 micro-Volt, yielding a total range of 0 to +6.55 Volts.

acdSfpDiagLbc.name: acdSfpDiagLbc
acdSfpDiagLbc.description: Measured TX bias current in micro-Amps yielding a total range of 0 to 131 mA.

acdSfpDiagTxPwr.name: acdSfpDiagTxPwr
acdSfpDiagTxPwr.description: Measured TX output power in mW. Represented as a 16 bit unsigned integer with the power defined as the full 16 bit value (0 to 65535) with LSB equal to 0.1 micro-Watt, yielding a total range of 0 to 6.5535 mW (~ -40 to +8.2 dBm).

acdSfpDiagRxPwr.name: acdSfpDiagRxPwr
acdSfpDiagRxPwr.description: Measured Rx input power in mW. Represented as a 16 bit unsigned integer with the power defined as the full 16 bit value (0 to 65535) with LSB equal to 0.1 micro-Watt, yielding a total range of 0 to 6.5535 mW (~ -40 to +8.2 dBm).

acdSfpDiagTxPwrdBm.name: acdSfpDiagTxPwrdBm
acdSfpDiagTxPwrdBm.description: Measured TX output power in dBm (~ -40 to +8.2 dBm).

acdSfpDiagRxPwrdBm.name: acdSfpDiagRxPwrdBm
acdSfpDiagRxPwrdBm.description: Measured Rx input power in dBm (~ -40 to +8.2 dBm).
